The following sample code shows how to implement a background thread to monitor the cache and remove the expired content.

The sample shows how to systematically name the temporary files so that the expiry time is known by checking their names.

It also demonstrates how to make sure there are no residue left from previous executions in case of crash or unexpected termination as the process monitors everything including files from other sessions.

## Code

The sample application shows the files in the cache directory, refreshed every 5 seconds. At the start of the launch, it creates a sample cache file with 1 minute expiry time.

After running for one minute, you can see that the file gets removed by the background monitoring thread. Moreover, the phone gets turned off, app gets crashed, or for any other reason the cache file stays there, the next time the app is launched, it will get removed.

