Android 13 provides APIs to securely copy and paste information while protecting it from being revealed to unintended users. 

In case your application needs to copy sensitive information to the clipboard, before calling the `ClipboardManager#setPrimaryClip()` method must add the sensitive data flag to the clipboard. By adding this flag, you can prevent the sensitive content from being viewed in the content preview.

The following code snippet shows how to securely store sensitive information in the clipboard:

